description:
&lt;p&gt;Conquest Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff Nurse – Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Acute Assessment Unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;37.5 hours per week, Internal Rotation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to make a difference or take on a new challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether you are just starting out on your Nursing career, looking for a change of job, working in a Nursing Home or even returning to practice, we would welcome the opportunity to meet with you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AAU is an extremely busy 19 bedded ward that accepts patients for medical assessment from G.Ps and A&amp;E. We are looking for a Staff Nurse with Acute Care experience to complete our team, who will have excellent communication skills and the ability to develop and support students and staff with clinical expertise. You will also have the opportunity of working within our Same Day Emergency Care Clinic that also accepts patients for medical assessment from G.Ps and A&amp;E giving you a very varied workload. We are looking to expand and develop this area in the very near future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be expected to function effectively under pressure without compromising basic standards of care and professionalism. In return we will offer you excellent managerial support and commitment to your personal professional development. The team is both friendly and supportive, with a strong commitment to providing a high standard of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and dedication, East Sussex Healthcare Trust offers excellent opportunities for career progression and professional development as well as a personal Induction. There are opportunities to complete your advance Nurse Practitioner and Nurse prescriber course. Other opportunities include completing post graduate Degrees or Masters. All Nurse are given the Mentorship course and leadership programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In houses course included ALS/ILS, ALERT courses as well as many others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal discussion, please contact Daphne Carew Unit Matron, AAU Conquest – 01424-755255 Ext 7478&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
